<p>He nodded. â€œThank you, Mama. You lift us up, Mama!â€</p>
<p>As I expected, Samy shook his head and gave me a disapproving look. He pinched my earlobe. â€œMbindi, you know this is bordering on pathological, right?â€</p>
<p>He walked me to the bottom of the stairs where we were surrounded by his beds of African violets, his miracle babies. The barren soil just outside of the studio had yielded to the gentle persuasion of Samyâ€™s ï¬ngers. The intense purple of the little flowers, a surreal shade of indigo, stood out against the ochre floor and muddy water around them.</p>
<p>I shared Tashunâ€™s big idea with Samy. â€œMaybe if we talk to him together, heâ€™ll see that it makes no sense . . . You could tell himâ€”â€</p>
<p>â€œAs if your husband has ever taken me seriously! He only asks my opinion when it doesnâ€™t matter. It would be pointless, and you know it as well as I do.â€</p>
<p>The boys watched us impatiently, eager for me to leave. Samy hugged me and went back up the steps.</p>
<p>As I opened the car door, I heard him say behind me, â€œMbindi! <em>Ab amicis honesta petamus. </em>One should only ask from a friend what he is capable of!â€ Providence doesnâ€™t give you a Latin teacher for a mother without consequence: Samy declaimed classical locutions with scandalous ease.</p>
<p>I turned around, raised my right hand, and joined the tips of my thumb and index ï¬nger, my other digits raised to the sky. Samy smiled. As I brushed the fallen pink flame tree petals from the windshield and shooed away the stray dog who was urinating on my back tires, I wondered if Samy was alluding to my inability to gauge the quality of his work or to his inability to plead my cause to Tashun.</p>
<p class="p1" style="text-align: center;">__________________________________</p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><em>Excerpt from</em> <a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9781566897457" class="external" target="_blank">The Aquatics</a><em>Â by Osvalde Lewat, translated by Maren Baudet-Lackner (Coffee House Press, 2025). Reprinted with permission of publisher.</em></p>
